{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5319cc1d-16eb-4f40-be52-ff0913b29160","content":"Here's the recommended setup:\n\n## 1. Project file (`MyTests.csproj`)\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"Microsoft.NET.Sdk\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n    <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.*\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThe `MSTest` meta-package pulls in the framework, test adapter, and runner. `EnableMSTestRunner` gives you the newer in-process runner.\n\n## 2. Enable parallel execution (`.runsettings`)\n\nCreate a `*.runsettings` file at the project root:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"utf-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <Parallelize>\n      <Workers>0</Workers>          <!-- 0 = match CPU count -->\n      <Scope>MethodLevel</Scope>    <!-- or ClassLevel -->\n    </Parallelize>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\nAlternatively, skip the `.runsettings` file and add a single assembly-level attribute in a file like `TestConfig.cs`:\n\n```csharp\n[assembly: Parallelize(Workers = 0, Scope = ExecutionScope.Method)]\n```\n\n## 3. Run database tests sequentially\n\nMark your database test class with `[DoNotParallelize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\n[DoNotParallelize]\npublic class DatabaseIntegrationTests\n{\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Insert_Then_Read_ReturnsExpected() { /* ... */ }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void Delete_NonExistent_ThrowsNotFound() { /* ... */ }\n}\n```\n\n**How it works:** All other test classes run in parallel. Classes marked `[DoNotParallelize]` are queued and run one at a time *after* the parallel batch finishes, so there's no risk of concurrent DB access.\n\n**Key points:**\n- `Workers = 0` auto-scales to your CPU core count.\n- `Scope = Method` parallelizes across methods (max parallelism). Use `Class` if tests within a class share state.\n- `[DoNotParallelize]` can go on a class or an individual `[TestMethod]`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8b1fdc5b-5cd3-4982-8865-302d50c5d780","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory appears empty. The user is asking a general knowledge question about setting up an MSTest project. Let me provide the recommended setup based on my knowledge of MSTest.","outputTokens":651,"requestId":"1BC1:23CF76:23DA330:279CDA0:6A03DA2D"},"id":"6d960c0f-747a-4668-b2a3-bb763d6f5b16","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:56:10.962Z","parentId":"892a30a4-de09-460d-b17b-aab6c36498d7"}
